      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: justify;">The first thing that comes to your mind when you hear the concept of “water gas hybrid cars” is, does run your car on water work? Well, at present over 10,000 cars are running on commercial roots which have been fit with these kits. So yes, this expression <a href="http://1r9u8l9x.centemax.hop.clickbank.net/?tid=1O" target="_blank"><strong>Run Cars On Water</strong></a> is completely true and you can have your own car running on water too with this run your car on water kit.</p>
<p>The hybrid cars do not require any compromise in terms of performance or power either.The basic technology of extracting hydrogen gas from water has been around for a long time but it was the recent testing which made this technology commercially available. Nowadays there are a lot of speculations on the hybrid kits available in the markets.</p>
<p>Water gas hybrid kits operate on a simple principle of breaking down water into HHO cells using electrostatic charges. These cells although are incombustible but they aid combustion of other fuels, i.e. HHO cells aid complete combustion of fuels in the engine.</p>
<p>The proper combustion of fuels not only <a href="http://1r9u8l9x.centemax.hop.clickbank.net/?tid=1O" target="_blank"><strong>increases the mileage of the car</strong></a> but also leads to reduced emissions, making your car eco-friendly. Hybrid kits are placed at $600 under various offers and schemes on the net. However here you can avail this kit under $50. In addition to this, these kits do not require any maintenance.</p>
<p>Seeing the rise in prices of crude oil, hybrid cars are surely deemed to attract a lot of people. If you are among those people who have to keep constant track of fuel gauze to check consumption then hybrid kit is ideal for you. <a href="http://1r9u8l9x.centemax.hop.clickbank.net/?tid=1O" target="_blank"><strong>Running a car on water</strong></a> is not an impossible thing to do and you can learn all the instructions from a guide called &#8221; Run Your Car On Water&#8221;</p>
